channel.title: Devilscape Compiler Error
channel.description:
Ok I get this error while trying to compile the client. I just downloaded the client and touched nothing but the compiler's info (JDK) Please Help :D
src\Class30.java:15: error: cannot find symbol return JSObject.getWindow(arg0).call(arg2, null); ^ symbol: method getWindow(Applet) location: class JSObject src\Class30.java:25: error: cannot find symbol JSObject.getWindow(arg2).eval(arg1); ^ symbol: method getWindow(Applet) location: class JSObject src\Class30.java:36: error: cannot find symbol return JSObject.getWindow(arg0).call(arg3, arg1); ^ symbol: method getWindow(Applet) location: class JSObject Note: src\Class108.java uses or overrides a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. 3 errors Press any key to continue . . .
I tried doing it Eclipse like runeball said and that's what I got (second image) :P Any help? Sorry I'm totally new to Eclipse :P Thanks!

item.title: Devilscape Compiler Error
item.dc:creator: @runeball runeball
item.description:
@runeball wrote:

the best thing of a compiler is it shows ur errors.

if i was u i would set up the source in Eclipse.

and go look at the lines

src\Class30.java:15

src\Class30.java:25:

src\Class30.java:36:

on each line in the compiler u see an error.

first line u can’t find the symbol mostly of the time its just somewhere else around that look for missing symbols or wrongcoded items.

i think its ur override whats making this error.

Note: src\Class108.java uses or overrides a deprecated API.

if i was you check that in eclipse and delete it so it don’t override.

i don’t say it will fix ur error but its somewhere in one of the classes the compiler says in ur error.

next time give some more information please. like what did u try to let it work. a part of coding from the classes where the errors are.

for people (like me) that are new to this we can do almost nothing with information like this. people with more skills in this will know it but maybe they don’t react because they want u to search for urself.
